ght\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h1\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Indoor Dog Park in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania\\\"}],\\\"$undefined\\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-description\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Whether you are hiking the vast trails of Wissahickon Valley or relaxing in Rittenhouse Square, Philadelphia blends history with high-quality pet amenities.\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"city-rich-description\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-description-paragraph\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Philadelphia, the City of Brotherly Love, extends that affection to its canine residents through a wealth of urban green spaces and historic charm. Adventurous pups will love \\\",null,[\\\"$\\\",\\\"strong\\\",\\\"2\\\",{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Wissahickon Valley Park\\\"}],\\\", which boasts over 50 miles of trails, including the scenic Forbidden Drive. In the heart of the city, \\\",null,[\\\"$\\\",\\\"strong\\\",\\\"5\\\",{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Schuylkill River Park\\\"}],\\\" offers a popular enclosed dog run with separate sections for small and large breeds, ensuring a safe environment for all. For a more relaxed afternoon, leashed dogs are welcome in the historic \\\",null,[\\\"$\\\",\\\"strong\\\",\\\"8\\\",{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Rittenhouse Square\\\"}],\\\" or can join you for a stroll through the \\\",null,[\\\"$\\\",\\\"strong\\\",\\\"11\\\",{\\\"children\\\":\\\"9th Street Italian Market\\\"}],\\\". Philadelphia’s leash laws require a six-foot lead in all public areas unless specified as an off-leash zone, and the city strictly enforces waste removal to keep its parks beautiful.\\\"]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-description-paragraph\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"The \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L12\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://phillypaws.org/\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-link\\\",\